### ğŸ“Œ What is a Variable?
- A variable is a container used to store data.

### ğŸ§  Rules for Variables
- No spaces (  begin with a letter (a-z, A-Z) or an underscore (_) , The rest of the name can include letters, digits (0-9), and underscores.
- Variable names are case-sensitive (e.g., Rahul and rahul are different variables)
- Cannot start with a number
- Use meaningful names
- Avoid keywords ( Variable names should not be the same as any Python keyword ) 
- Camel Case: myVariableName ,  Pascal Case: MyVariableName ,  Snake Case: my_variable_name

### Types of variables
- Local Variables: Declared inside a function and can only be accessed within that function.
- Global Variables: Declared outside any function and can be accessed globally throughout the program.

### ğŸ“Š Data Types in Python 
| Data Type | Example     |
| --------- | ----------- |
| int       | 10, 100     |
| float     | 10.5, 3.14  |
| str       | "Hello"     |
| bool      | True, False |
| NoneType  | None        |

